(x,y)
m_1(x,y)=m_2(x,y)
 m_1(x,y) = \frac{y}{x-4/3}. 
 Df(x,y) = \left(\begin{array}{c}6x \\ -2y\end{array}\right) 
   \left(\begin{array}{c}2y \\ 6x\end{array}\right) 
 m_2(x,y) = \frac{6x}{2y}. 
 \begin{cases} \frac{y}{x-4/3} = \frac{3x}{y}\\ 3x^2 - y^2 = 8 \end{cases} 
